## SECTION 1: IMPORTS & EXPORTS

- [ ] Every import at top of file — no require() inside components or functions
- [ ] No duplicate imports of same module
- [ ] Every imported name is actually used
- [ ] Every used name is actually imported (no assumed globals)
- [ ] Named vs default exports match at call sites
- [ ] File extensions correct (.js vs .jsx vs .mjs vs .ts)
- [ ] No circular imports between files
- [ ] ESM (import/export) and CJS (require) not mixed in same file
- [ ] .mjs extension used for ESM scripts run directly by Node
- [ ] package.json “type”:“module” not set if react-scripts used (breaks build)
- [ ] Third-party packages installed in package.json dependencies
- [ ] Package versions compatible with each other
- [ ] No importing from private/internal package paths that may change

-----

## SECTION 2: REACT HOOKS RULES

- [ ] No hooks called inside if/else/ternary/switch/loops
- [ ] No hooks called conditionally — always called in same order every render
- [ ] No hooks inside nested functions inside components
- [ ] useEffect cleanup returned for every effect with timers, listeners, subscriptions
- [ ] useEffect dependency array includes EVERY variable/function referenced inside
- [ ] useCallback dependency array includes EVERY variable referenced inside
- [ ] useMemo dependency array includes EVERY variable referenced inside
- [ ] No stale closures — state from old render not used in async callbacks
- [ ] No setState called after component unmounts (use isMounted / aborted flag)
- [ ] useState initial values are correct type
- [ ] useRef used for values that should NOT cause re-renders
- [ ] No direct mutation of state variables — always use setter
- [ ] React.memo used on expensive child components with stable props
- [ ] Context values memoized to prevent unnecessary re-renders
- [ ] useLayoutEffect only when DOM measurement needed — not as substitute for useEffect

-----

## SECTION 3: ASYNC / PROMISES

- [ ] Every async function has try/catch or .catch() handler
- [ ] No unhandled promise rejections
- [ ] await used on every Promise where result or timing matters
- [ ] Intentional fire-and-forget clearly commented
- [ ] AbortController used for fetch calls that should be cancellable
- [ ] Race conditions guarded with aborted/isMounted flags in async useEffects
- [ ] Promise.all() used for independent parallel operations (not sequential awaits)
- [ ] Error objects have .message extracted before display to user
- [ ] No top-level await in non-module files
- [ ] Promise chains not mixed with async/await in same function

