## SECTION 4: NULL / UNDEFINED SAFETY

- [ ] No .property access on value that could be null or undefined
- [ ] No array methods called on non-array values
- [ ] Optional chaining (?.) used where object may not exist
- [ ] Nullish coalescing (??) vs OR (||) correct — 0 and ‘’ are falsy, not nullish
- [ ] Function arguments validated before destructuring or property access
- [ ] Array.find() result checked before accessing properties on it
- [ ] JSON.parse() wrapped in try/catch
- [ ] localStorage.getItem() null-checked before JSON.parse()
- [ ] publicKey null-checked before .toString() — Solana wallets return null before connect
- [ ] evmAddress null-checked before string operations
- [ ] walletClient null-checked before calling methods
- [ ] API response bodies null-checked before accessing .routes/.data/.result
- [ ] Nested optional fields use ?. (e.g. step?.action?.fromChainId)

