## SECTION 5: TYPE SAFETY

- [ ] BigInt() NEVER called on float strings — Math.floor().toString() first
- [ ] BigInt() NEVER called on undefined, null, NaN, or decimal numbers
- [ ] parseInt() ALWAYS has radix (parseInt(x, 16) not parseInt(x))
- [ ] parseFloat() result checked isNaN() before arithmetic
- [ ] typeof check before type-sensitive operations
- [ ] === strict equality used, never == (no implicit type coercion)
- [ ] String vs number for chain IDs consistent — LiFi returns numbers, wagmi uses numbers
- [ ] Array.isArray() checked before .map/.filter/.reduce
- [ ] Token decimals always have fallback — dec(token) helper, never raw .decimals
- [ ] Math.pow(10, decimals) always has integer decimals (NaN if undefined)
- [ ] Number.isFinite() check for values used in financial calculations
- [ ] No implicit string-to-number coercion in arithmetic (+str, str*1)

